com.prc.alp.liaison.plugin
Class LiaisonManager

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--com.prc.alp.liaison.plugin.LiaisonManager
public class LiaisonManager
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Runnable, LiaisonTrigger

Supports the establishment of contact and the administration of interactions between a PlugIn and agents in some external agent society. LiaisonManager instances are the focal object for representing a PlugIn as a single agent for purposes of liaison permission administration.

LiaisonManager

public LiaisonManager(org.cougaar.core.cluster.ClusterServesPlugIn cluster,
                      java.lang.String community,
                      java.lang.String societyURI,
                      java.lang.String locatorRef)
A constructor for LiaisonManager that must be called from a PlugIn
Parameters:
cluster - a PlugInAdapter identifying the caller as an agent representing a particular ALP cluster.
community - a String identifying the ALP community to which the caller belongs.
societyURI - a URI String identifying the ALP society to which the caller belongs.
locatorRef - A URL for the Jini lookup service to search for a JavaSpace service through which liaison permissions will be administered

A PlugIn-independent constructor for a LiaisonManager
Parameters:
myName - a String identifying the caller as an agent in the context of some particular ALP society; need not be globally unique.
community - a String identifying the ALP community to which the caller belongs.
societyURI - a URI String identifying the ALP society to which the caller belongs.
locatorRef - A URL for the Jini lookup service to search for a JavaSpace service through which liaison permissions will be administered
